 and contributed to the sending regions’ socioeconomic development. Dear China contributes substantially to our understanding of modern Chinese history and to the comparative study of global migration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Dez 2022) 0aChinesezForeign countriesxCorrespondence. 0aChinesezForeign countriesxHistory. 0aEmigrant remittanceszChinaxHistoryy19th century. 0aEmigrant remittanceszChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aEmigrant remittanceszChinay19th century. 0aEmigrant remittanceszChinay20th century. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh  a19th century.  a20th century.  achanging history.  achinese diaspora.  achinese emigrants.  across national mechanisms.  aglobal migration.  ainstitutionalized.  aletters cum remittances.  amodern chinese history.  aoperations.  aorigins.  aqiaopi trade.  aqiaopi.  aseparated by distance.  asilver letters.  asocioeconomic development.  astate frontiers.  astructure.  asustain families.  atransformations.1 aGungwu, Wang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiu, Hong, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106676770 cprintz978052029841540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520970540423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520970540/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY